  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 180°C/ 160°C (fan)/ gas 4, and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lamb-and-courgette-ragu-with-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s] </strong>in half lengthways, then slice into half moons</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lamb-and-courgette-ragu-with-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> to the onion and cook for 3-4 min,<strong> </strong>breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go, or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lamb-and-courgette-ragu-with-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lamb-and-courgette-ragu-with-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>beef stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> to the pan and cook for 15-20 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese sauce-like consistency and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>sauce</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lamb-and-courgette-ragu-with-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> wholewheat tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain and reserve a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lamb-and-courgette-ragu-with-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> to the<strong> sauce</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if it's looking a little dry!</p><p>Season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> Tuscan-style lamb & roasted courgette ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tuscan-style-lamb-and-courgette-ragu-with-wholewheat-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked wholewheat tortiglioni </strong>to the pan with the <strong>Tuscan-style lamb & roasted courgette ragù </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce</p><p>Serve in a bowl, garnished with the <strong>chopped basil</strong> and<strong> </strong>your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
